Hi Dave,

I&#39;m following up on the memory problems with the multi-phase
equilibrium solver.  For reference, we are using Cantera in Matlab to
do straight-up equilibrium calculations, using various different
species data files.  We do some of these calculations at constant T,P
with T &lt; 300K, which appears to require use of the &quot;second&quot;
equilibrium solver (third argument to equilibrate.m = 1).

Here is a MATLAB script which demonstrates the memory leak.  If you
are using Windows, the &#39;Performance&#39; tab in the Task Manager will show
a significant increase in Page File usage when this script is run. 
That memory is not freed up until Matlab is exited (even when using
the &#39;clear&#39; and &#39;cleanup&#39; commands).

However, if you change the 3rd argument to &#39;equilibrate&#39; to a 0
(zero), the script will not use up any apprciable memory.

---

G = IdealGasMix(&#39;gri30.xml&#39;);
iCH4 = speciesIndex(G,&#39;CH4&#39;);
iO2 = speciesIndex(G,&#39;O2&#39;);
iN2 = speciesIndex(G,&#39;N2&#39;);

Xin = zeros(size(moleFractions(G)));
Xin(iO2) = 1;
Xin(iN2) = 3.76;
T1 = 400;
P1 = 2*oneatm;

phiArray = [0.25 0.5 0.75 0.95 1.05 1.5 2];
TArray = zeros(size(phiArray));

for i = 1:length(phiArray)
    Xin(iCH4) = phiArray(i)/2;
    set(G,&#39;X&#39;,Xin,&#39;T&#39;,T1,&#39;P&#39;,P1);
    equilibrate(G,&#39;HP&#39;,1);                    %% CHANGE THIS LINE
    TArray(i) = temperature(G);
end

plot(phiArray,TArray)

---

Let me know if there is anything I or my coworkers can do to help
improve the functionality of solver #1.

